extends layout

block content
  h1= title

  div Welcome to #{title} / #{finalRate}
    div.progress
      div.progress-bar.progress-bar-danger(style="width: #{countFalse}0%")
        span.sr-only 40% Invalid points

      div.progress-bar.progress-bar-warning(style="width: #{countUnknown}0%")
        span.sr-only 10% Unknow points

      div.progress-bar.progress-bar-success(style="width: #{countTrue}0%")
        span.sr-only 50% Valid points


  div#accordion(role="tablist")
    div.card
      div#headingOne.card-header(role="tab", data-pass="#{validationOne.valid}")
        h5.mb-0
          span.badge 1
          a(data-toggle="collapse", href="#collapseOne", aria-expanded="false", aria-controls="collapseOne") Be skeptical of headlines.

      div#collapseOne.collapse(role="tabpanel", aria-labelledby="headingOne", data-parent="#accordion")
        div.card-body
          False news stories often have catchy headlines in all caps with exclamation points. If shocking claims in the headline sound unbelievable, they probably are.

    div.card
      div#headingTwo.card-header(role="tab", data-pass="#{validationTwo.valid}")
        h5.mb-0
          span.badge 2
          a(data-toggle="collapse", href="#collapseTwo", aria-expanded="false", aria-controls="collapseTwo") Look closely at the URL.

      div#collapseTwo.collapse(role="tabpanel", aria-labelledby="headingTwo", data-parent="#accordion")
        div.card-body
          A phony or look-alike URL may be a warning sign of false news. Many false news sites mimic authentic news sources by making small changes to the URL. You can go to the site to compare the URL to established sources.

     div.card
      div#headingThree.card-header(role="tab", data-pass="#{validationThree.valid}")
        h5.mb-0
          span.badge 3
          a(data-toggle="collapse", href="#collapseThree", aria-expanded="false", aria-controls="collapseThree") Investigate the source.

      div#collapseThree.collapse(role="tabpanel", aria-labelledby="headingThree", data-parent="#accordion")
        div.card-body
          Ensure that the story is written by a source that you trust with a reputation for accuracy. If the story comes from an unfamiliar organization, check their "About" section to learn more.

     div.card
      div#headingFour.card-header(role="tab", data-pass="#{validationFour.valid}")
        h5.mb-0
          span.badge 4
          a(data-toggle="collapse", href="#collapseFour", aria-expanded="false", aria-controls="collapseFour") Watch for unusual formatting.

      div#collapseFour.collapse(role="tabpanel", aria-labelledby="headingFour", data-parent="#accordion")
        div.card-body
          Many false news sites have misspellings or awkward layouts. Read carefully if you see these signs.

     div.card
      div#headingFive.card-header(role="tab", data-pass="#{validationFive.valid}")
        h5.mb-0
          span.badge 5
          a(data-toggle="collapse", href="#collapseFive", aria-expanded="false", aria-controls="collapseFive") Consider the photos.

      div#collapseFive.collapse(role="tabpanel", aria-labelledby="headingFive", data-parent="#accordion")
        div.card-body
          False news stories often contain manipulated images or videos. Sometimes the photo may be authentic, but taken out of context. You can search for the photo or image to verify where it came from.

     div.card
      div#headingSix.card-header(role="tab", data-pass="#{validationSix.valid}")
        h5.mb-0
          span.badge 6
          a(data-toggle="collapse", href="#collapseSix", aria-expanded="false", aria-controls="collapseSix") Inspect the dates.

      div#collapseSix.collapse(role="tabpanel", aria-labelledby="headingSix", data-parent="#accordion")
        div.card-body
          False news stories may contain timelines that make no sense, or event dates that have been altered.

     div.card
      div#headingSeven.card-header(role="tab", data-pass="#{validationSeven.valid}")
        h5.mb-0
          span.badge 7
          a(data-toggle="collapse", href="#collapseSeven", aria-expanded="false", aria-controls="collapseSeven") Check the evidence.

      div#collapseSeven.collapse(role="tabpanel", aria-labelledby="headingSeven", data-parent="#accordion")
        div.card-body
          Check the author's sources to confirm that they are accurate. Lack of evidence or reliance on unnamed experts may indicate a false news story.

     div.card
      div#headingEight.card-header(role="tab", data-pass="#{validationEight.valid}")
        h5.mb-0
          span.badge 8
          a(data-toggle="collapse", href="#collapseEight", aria-expanded="false", aria-controls="collapseEight") Look at other reports.

      div#collapseEight.collapse(role="tabpanel", aria-labelledby="headingEight", data-parent="#accordion")
        div.card-body
          If no other news source is reporting the same story, it may indicate that the story is false. If the story is reported by multiple sources you trust, it's more likely to be true.

     div.card
      div#headingNine.card-header(role="tab", data-pass="#{validationNine.valid}")
        h5.mb-0
          span.badge 9
          a(data-toggle="collapse", href="#collapseNine", aria-expanded="false", aria-controls="collapseNine") Is the story a joke?

      div#collapseNine.collapse(role="tabpanel", aria-labelledby="headingNine", data-parent="#accordion")
        div.card-body
          Sometimes false news stories can be hard to distinguish from humor or satire. Check whether the source is known for parody, and whether the story's details and tone suggest it may be just for fun.

     div.card
      div#headingTen.card-header(role="tab", data-pass="#{validationTen.valid}")
        h5.mb-0
          span.badge 10
          a(data-toggle="collapse", href="#collapseTen", aria-expanded="false", aria-controls="collapseTen") Some stories are intentionally false.

      div#collapseTen.collapse(role="tabpanel", aria-labelledby="headingTen", data-parent="#accordion")
        div.card-body
          Think critically about the stories you read, and only share news that you know to be credible.

  div.footer
